Aperture fully supports app-controlled follow cameras. The camera entity is spawned via `spawn.camera()` with initial fov and clearColor. Each frame, a system retrieves the camera and player entities by Name, computes the desired camera position using deadzone and velocity lead math (matching the reference), and directly updates the camera's LocalTransform.translation and LocalTransform.rotation each frame via component views. The engine has no built-in camera controller fighting the app.

Example (analogous to Racing reference):
